# AlphaGo versus Ke Jie

The **AlphaGo versus Ke Jie** match was a historic three-game [Go](/Go_(game)) encounter between [AlphaGo Master](/AlphaGo_Master), an artificial intelligence program developed by [DeepMind](/DeepMind), and [Ke Jie](/Ke_Jie), the world's top-ranked human Go player at the time. The match took place from **23 to 27 May 2017** as part of the [Future of Go Summit](/Future_of_Go_Summit) in [Wuzhen](/Wuzhen), China. AlphaGo emerged victorious in all three games, marking a definitive milestone in the intersection of artificial intelligence and traditional board games.

